lead_paragraph: We have received by the Illinois advices from Oregon City to the 5th of August. Emigrants still continued to pour in. The Oregon Spectator mentions the arrival, on the 1st., of Mr. F. L. RAYMOND, of Indiana, one of a company of packers. About a hundred teams had started with him from St. Joseph's for Oregon. The Spectator gives the following outline of his journey:

headline.main: FROM OREGON.; FROM SOUTH AMERICA. FROM THE SANDWICH ISLANDS AUSTRALIA.
